":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage"},{"text":" persistence strategies.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tools of version 1.9. See "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Sharing state","type":"heading","anchor":"Sharing-state"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"text":" property wrapper:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This will require that ","type":"text"},{"code":"SignUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, if you want any","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and specify a URL:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Upon app launch the ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in the application will automatically update."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appStorage"}